                            <comment id="13891" author="shaug" created="Thu, 14 Jul 2005 02:47:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Um, somehow I set the component to SpringWEBFLOW. I thought I had set it to SpringCORE. My apologies...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13892" author="shaug" created="Thu, 14 Jul 2005 02:48:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ugh. I shouldn&apos;t file bugs until I&apos;ve had my coffee. The bug title should be &quot;factory-bean not allowed on anonymous bean&quot;, not &quot;... anonymous class&quot;. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ugh.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13939" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Tue, 19 Jul 2005 07:37:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for pointing this out! I&apos;ve added a corresponding name generation strategy for beans with &quot;factory-bean&quot; declaration.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The previous ones were only able to work on bean class or parent name, requiring one of those to be declared for an anonymous bean definition.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
